data.description: Simply spectacular home in Traditions of Braselton! This gorgeous 5BR/4.5BA home sits on a full unfinished basement. Step on to the covered front porch and into the grand two-story entry with stunning hardwood floors. Just off the entry is a formal Dining Room that boasts trey ceiling, crown moulding and lots of natural light. Just across the entry is the formal Living Room which would make a great office, study or library. Continue in to the Great Room that features coffered ceiling, built-in bookshelves, stone fireplace and opens to the Kitchen. The chef's Kitchen offers everything to host your friends and family - from the huge Kitchen island to the double ovens - and tons of cabinet and counter space. Just of the Kitchen is a cozy breakfast nook. Master on the Main is your own private retreat. This oversized Bedroom provides a sitting area, unique domed trey ceiling and a Master Spa Bath with soaking tub, separate oversized shower, and a custom dual vanity. Master closet has built-in shelves, organizers and cabinets. Upstairs, you will find a study desk area with cabinets - perfect for students or for working from home. Continuing thru the upstairs, there are four additional Bedrooms - each generously sized - as well as a media room/play room. The full Basement is unfinished and ready for your plans to extend your living space! Outside a screened in porch just off the Kitchen on the main level also has access from the Master Suite. A perfect spot for your morning coffee or unwinding at the end of the day. The Screened porch has stairs that lead to the Terrace level covered patio that overlooks your backyard oasis! Heated saltwater pool with attached jacuzzi hot tub is surrounded by a stone deck and features an extended sun bathing area on the deck. Traditions of Braselton is a golf club community that includes Junior Olympic sized pool with waterslide, kids splash zone, playground, fitness center, tennis courts, pickleball courts and optional golf memberships. The community is located convenient to I-85, shopping, restaurants and a golf cart ride away from local schools.
